<h1>Easily Allocate Parts of a Bank Transaction to Different Expenses</h1>

<p>
In personal finance management, many real-world purchases involve multiple types of expenses within a single bank transaction. Learning how to allocate portions of one transaction to different expense categories helps maintain accurate financial records and provides deeper insights into spending behavior.
</p>

<p>
For example, a single purchase at a supermarket might include groceries, household supplies, and personal care products. By dividing the total amount into multiple categories, your financial records become more precise and your spending analysis becomes much more meaningful.
</p>

